:status: published

FreeBSD has jails, and it has several commands that take a ``-j``
switch. Like if you want to start and stop services in a jail, you can
``service -j 3 stop httpd`` or so. Or ``pkg -j 3 install
myfunpackage``. I just got AIDE, whose configuration file has a bunch
of pathnames in it, like ``/etc`` or ``/usr/bin``. There's 